Source: https://github.com/harblaith7/React-Testing-Library-Net-Ninja

The core library, DOM testing library

The core library has been wrapped to provide ergonomic APIs for several frameworks, including React, Angular, and Vue. 

// screen.debug();

dependencies:
"@testing-library/jest-dom": "^5.16.4",
"@testing-library/react": "^12.1.2",
"@testing-library/user-event": "^12.1.2",

// Three types of test : unit, integration and E2E
unit : one component
integration: Interaction b/w multiple components
E2E: Testing end to end all the features available in the product

// Test block

1. Render a component that needs to be tested
2. Find the elements we want to interact with
3. Interact with the elements (click, change, drag events etc)
4. Assert that the results are as expected